      "lesson title": "Cybersecurity Risks in Public Sector AI Systems",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Public sector organisations are increasingly adopting artificial intelligence to deliver essential services, from healthcare and benefits processing to law enforcement and infrastructure management. This lesson introduces the key cybersecurity risks that arise when AI systems are deployed in these high risk environments, including data breaches, adversarial attacks, and the misuse of automated decision-making. You will explore real-world examples of how vulnerabilities in AI systems can disrupt critical services and undermine public trust. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of the threat landscape and the practical steps organisations can take to protect their AI-powered systems and the citizens who depend on them.",
      "status": "draft",
